reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Great fruity flavor packed with all the vitamins you need on a daily basis. Texture isn't gritty or tough. Great vitamins for the money! Good buy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These vitamins are a good value for the money. What I really like is that they are soft gummies instead of the harder sticky ones that almost take the crowns out of your mouth. Very easy vitamin to chew up.I also like the taste not to strong just the right amount.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I used this product as a daily multivitamin as a woman to give myself hopefully the vitamins and minerals that I may lack from my diet. I use this product to keep up my overall health. I liked the price. I did a fair amount of comparison shopping and found that these were the cheapest at the time. They are all pretty much the same color, but come in different shapes. They have a mildly sour taste (like sour gummies), which surprised me. I had never had gummy vitamins with this taste before. The texture is good and not weird. They are not super stuck together in the bottle. So far they have been working fine. They kind of make me want other sour sweets, but I usually eat a couple packs of regular fruit snacks and get over it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love the how sour they are!
reviews.reviewText: I don’t recommend these if u hate sour candies or anything sour in general, cus they are sour! But I love the sourness and the hint of fruitiness as well. I’ve only been taking them for 2 days now, mainly cus I have a terrible diet and I’m needing a lot more vitamins so I don’t get a deficiency! I once felt terrible cus of a vitamin D deficiency (photo shows the different shapes and textures, not the amount ur supposed to take daily)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Very nice product. Love the quality of these gummies. If you're living in a country with hot climate, trust and believe these gummies won't melt and stick together. The flavors are so good. definitely worth buying.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Yummy Gummies for Better Health
reviews.reviewText: These have pretty good taste if you like gummy fruit snacks. Instructions were to take 2 per day. I keep them in a room with temps 65-80 degrees F this season and they are sticking a little to the bottom and each other. So far, I've been able to just shake the container and they come apart. When the humid summer comes, I suspect they might stick a little more and need a fork/knife to dislodge and mix up. They are, thus far, keeping their shape. Store in a non-humid environment for best longevity. They were a good deal and I plan to purchase again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I’ve tried quite a few gummy vitamins before and these are the most sour! I have a hard time getting them down. My son loves sour candy so he thinks they’re great. If you tend to pucker with sour tastes then these are not for you. Other than taste, they stay pretty soft and are a great price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Tasty and Easy to Take
reviews.reviewText: I've started adding a few supplements to my diet and I really like these Amazon Basics gummies.They taste great and they are so easy to take. They are fresh and soft, unlike some gummy vitamins I've had that were super hard and perhaps stale.I also like the gummy vitamins as opposed to a tablet because I'm never sure if the tablet ever fully dissolves.With these gummies, I'm sure they are dissolved because you chew them before swallowing.They tastes like a berry candy so it would be hard not to like them. LolI added them to my subscriptions so they'll be delivered automatically.I hope this was helpful.
